parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Floor Mat Interference with Accelerator Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The floor mat can interfere with the accelerator pedal, causing unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal gets stuck
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates even when the brake pedal is pressed
the floor mat slips underneath the accelerator pedal
the driver is unable to control the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the strut tower/dome can lead to unsafe driving conditions, affecting the suspension, alignment, and tires, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Cracking of the strut tower/dome
uneven tire wear
bald tires
control arm failure
and alignment issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to address recall campaigns can lead to unsafe driving conditions, accidents, or injuries due to unresolved issues with vehicle speed control, suspension, power train, seats, electrical system, and fuel system.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the failure to address recall campaigns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end alignment issues can lead to uneven tire wear, bald tires, and unsafe driving conditions, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear
bald tires
and front end alignment issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turbo Waste Gate Actuator Connection Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty connection of the turbo waste gate actuator can cause the waste gates to fail to open, leading to engine damage, decreased performance, and potentially catastrophic engine failure.
symptoms: Rattling or unusual noise coming from the turbo area
waste gate failure to open
decreased engine performance
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The low engine oil warning can indicate a serious issue with the engine's lubrication system, potentially leading to engine damage or failure if not addressed promptly.
symptoms: Low engine oil warning light or message on the dashboard
low engine oil level
engine noise or knocking
engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the rear view camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries, especially when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear view camera displays a black screen
the rear view camera stops working intermittently
the rear view camera fails to display an image.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in ensuring that the front doors are closed can lead to accidents or injuries, especially if the doors open while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The front doors are difficult to close
the front doors do not latch properly
the front doors do not stay closed even when slammed shut.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended shift into park can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into park unexpectedly
the vehicle shifts into park at low speeds
the vehicle shifts into park from both the D and R gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power to turn off fully can cause the vehicle's systems to remain active, which can lead to battery drain, increased risk of theft, or other safety issues.
symptoms: The power does not turn off fully when exiting the vehicle
the power remains on even when the doors are locked and keys are outside the car.
